  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nThere's no visible way to distinguish new chats that appeared on your list. A message from a new contact or an invitation to join a group chat might go unnoticed.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1020\" alt=\"Screenshot 2020-02-26 at 14 48 10\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/75350942-9d4be180-58a7-11ea-9a17-3b955f0f2db3.png\">\r\n\r\nTo identify new chats on a list, please change the background colour of the list item to our `Light Blue`. This should persist until you open the chat for the first time, after which it returns to usual white. This affects new private chats that appeared on your list and new group chats.\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nNew chats are identified with the light blue background until they're opened.\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\n",
